			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Interesting observations, Larysa. I am not a student of Markov Logic, but as I read this post, particularly the description of the declarative nature of the tool, I wondered about a clojure implementation. The core.logic library is getting lots of attention these days and cascalog might be just the DSL to enable processing in a declarative style at scale.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

